# =============================================================================
# ServiceCycle — environment template
#
# This stub exists so a `cp .env.example .env` from the repo root produces a
# meaningful pointer instead of a stale, misleading config. The CANONICAL
# template is server/.env.example. Copy that file when bootstrapping a real
# deployment:
#
#     cp server/.env.example .env
#
# server/.env.example documents every variable ServiceCycle reads (Postgres, JWT,
# MASTER_KEY, email, AI provider, storage, demo mode, rate limiting,
# observability). The compose stack will refuse to start without
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD, JWT_SECRET (≥32 chars), and MASTER_KEY set.
#
# Generate secrets:
#   JWT_SECRET:      node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('base64'))"
#   MASTER_KEY:      node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"
#   POSTGRES_PASSWORD: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(24).toString('base64url'))"
#
# See docs/install.md for the operator install runbook and
# docs/operator-playbook.md for backup / restore / key-rotation procedures.
# =============================================================================
